text: Lets use this momentum to sustain peace!

text:

3 key points to sustain peace:
#1. It must be a part of our comprehensive response to this pandemic.
#2. It requires synergy between the works of all UN system; and
#3. Smart use of resources

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#Tifa in #Maluku is tubular w/o handles & is divided into several types: Jekir, Potong, Dasar, Bass. Those types are distinguished by the sound color, thus when played together, there's a specific function to each accord. to the sound color.

Photo credit: https://t.co/jNRegbI736 https://t.co/nmBf09oAAF

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Nevertheless, #Tifa musical instruments in #Papua & #Maluku have different forms. In Papua, the middle part of the #Tifa is more curved & has a handle on the middle part.

#digitallearning #digitaldiplomacy #publicdiplomacy #culturaldiplomacy #inidiplomasi #sARTurday #budayasaya https://t.co/4onk605Dqu

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#Tifa is not only well-known in #Papua. Another eastern province of #Indonesia, #Maluku (#Moluccas), also recognizes it as a #native #traditional #percussion wonder of the region.
#WonderfulIndonesia #IndonesianCulture #IndonesianArt #IndonesianWay #musicalinstruments #sARTurday https://t.co/jHfpnZrLFb

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:

text:
#Tifa is a type of musical instrument with only one sound, so it can be the main sound or the rhythm regulator when played w/ other #musicalinstruments.

#sARTurday #wonderfulindonesia #art #culture #music #inidiplomasi #publicdiplomacy #digitallearning #indonesianway #indonesia

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
This #instrument is similar to a #drum that is played by hitting on the surface. #Tifa is made from an empty piece of wood, both sides of which are removed & covered with dried deer skin to produce a vibrant & beautiful sound.

#indonesianway #culturalheritage #wonderfulindonesia https://t.co/BfJKBerkrp

text: During the presidency, Indonesia will focus on (1) Advancing the strengthening of peacebuilding efforts after the COVID-19 pandemic; (2) Strengthening efforts to address current security issues such as terrorism, cybersecurity and transnational crime in a comprehensive manner;

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
During the time of the #Sunda Kingdom (12th-16th century), #Angklung was played as a form of worship of Nyai Sri Pohaci, a Goddess of Fertility. It is also said that Angklung was played as a morale booster during wars.

Angklung photo & source: @indtravel

#WonderfulIndonesia

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
According to Jaap Kunst’s book “Music in Java”, besides West Java, #angklung can also be found in the regions of South #Sumatra & #Kalimantan, and the people of #Lampung, East Java, & Central #Java also use this instrument.
#traditionalmusic #indonesianculture #musicalinstruments

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Etymologically, #angklung comes fr the Sundanese word "angka", which means tone, and the word "lung", which means broken. Therefore, angklung means “a broken or incomplete tone.”

#IndonesianWay #DigitalDiplomacy #IniDiplomasi #CulturalDiplomacy #intangibleheritage #indonesianart

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
A traditional <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>instrument made of bamboo tubes, #Angklung, is often found in the area of #WestJava. A tune is produced by gently shaking the instrument so that the #bamboo tubes collide w/ each other.

#IndonesianWay #culturalheritage #WonderfulIndonesia @unesco

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9> #Kolintang is a wooden, pitched percussion #musicalinstrument originating fr #Minahasa area, North #Sulawesi. It's made of strong local wood w/ light fiber, i.a. Telur (Alstonia sp), Cempaka Elmerrillia Tsiampaca), Wenuang (Octomeles Sumatrana Miq), & Waru (Hibiscus Tiliaceus) https://t.co/gP8uZGvj6D

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Consisting of rows of horizontally-placed small gongs, #Kolintang / #kulintang is #musicalinstrument that hs been played for centuries in the East Malay regions-incl<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>-as part of Southeast Asian gong-chime #culture.
The performance is sometimes accomp. by larger hanging gong&drum

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Watch this wonderful rendition of "Indonesia Tanah Air Beta" (means 'Indonesia My Homeland') by Sasando master, Natalino Mella, to hear how beautiful & serene the sound of #Sasando.
https://t.co/0CeIDrBHpZ

#IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #CulturalHeritage @DigiDiplomats @digidiplo

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The #philosophy behind #Sasando’s shape&voice is unique; it has a special meaning in the lives of the ppl of #Rote island, East #NusaTenggara (#NTT). The 9strings present in the original form of Sasando used to symbolize the life cycle of a human child in the womb.
#IndonesianWay

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
At first, #Sasando only had 7-10 strings made out of natural materials. By the 18th century, more strings were added and the number increased 24 to 28. Nowadays, 32 to 48 strings are being used in a Sasando.

#IniDiplomasi #Indonesianculture #Indonesianway #musicalinstruments

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#Sasando is played using both hands & each hand picks in opposite directions. The right-hand plays the chord, while the left-hand picks the #melody and #bass. It requires a particular set of skills to play Sasando.

#IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #MusicalInstruments #IndonesianArt

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
@indtravel @budayasaya @digidiplo @DigiDiplomats @DCculture @mywhcc @EmbassyAdoption @Kemlu_RI @SmithsonianFolk @mullylingua Initially, #Sasando strings were made fr palm leaf sticks, but later got replaced by steel strings that were commonly used for violins after the Portuguese came to #Indonesia.
#IniDiplomasi #CulturalDiplomacy #PublicDiplomacy #WonderfulIndonesia #IndonesianWay #MusicalInstruments

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#Sasando is a traditional musical instrument fr East #NusaTenggara (NTT) made out of bamboo & palm leaves. It was created in the 17th century in Rote isl. by 2shepherds who realized that a soft tune could be produced by the container which was used to draw water.
<U+0001F4F8> by @indtravel https://t.co/2xhF2Q4Q9H

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Those #prevention #efforts hv enabled several provinces incl.#Riau,#Jambi,& #SouthSumatera to successfully overcome the “#first #critical #phase” of #land& #forest #fires fr March to early June this year.
#IndonesianWay #RintisKemajuan #HutanRiauBebasAsap #EnvironmentalInnovation

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The #early #detection was carried out i.a. by #educating the #traditional #farmers not to #clear #land by #burning,& by #creating the #artificial #rain as part of the #weather #modification to maintain the #peatlands & to fill #reservoirs& #canals with #water.
#IndonesianWay

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The integrated patrols involve personnels fr the Min. of #Environment& #Forestry,<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>Armed Forces,<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>Nat'l Police, & #community #orgs. The #lawenforcement & #community #participation are among the #key #elements of the patrols.
#IndonesianWay #RintisKemajuan #EnvironmentalInnovation

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>Govt hs focused the #prevention #efforts to the areas most susceptible to #forest fires, i.a. through integrated patrols,#hotspots #early-#detection,#quick #response prior to #crisis,& #instrument #development such as air #pollution #standards #index (ISPU).
#RintisKemajuan https://t.co/A4ccDW4bCY

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>Govt closely monitors the #healthprotocols strictly followed in those provinces, especially in #public places incl. #markets, #shopping #centers, #prayer #houses& #boarding #schools,#health #facilities,& #offices.
#NegaraMelindungi #COVID19indonesia #indonesiamelawancovid19

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The 8 provs r #Jakarta,#WestJava,#CentralJava,#EastJava,#NorthSumatera,#SouthSulawesi,#SouthKalimantan,& #Papua. According to<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>’s Central Statistics Agency,the combined population in those provs is more than 166million(70% of total population).
#NegaraMelindungi #COVID19indonesia

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
In line w/ the #redzone #mapping, Pres @Jokowi on July 27 requested that the #Committee for the #Covid19 Handling & Nat'l #EconomicRecovery prioritize mitigation efforts in 8 provinces reporting #high #positive #cases. 
#NegaraMelindungi #COVID19indonesia #indonesiamelawancovid19

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Those provs along w/respective redzones r North&SouthSumatera(5&1),North,SouthEast,&SouthSulawesi(3,1,&1),#Papua(1),WestNusaTenggara(2),East,Central,&SouthKalimantan(1,4,8),EastJava(9),CentralJava(8),Gorontalo(3),#Jakarta(5),& #Bali(1).
#COVID19indonesia #indonesiamelawancovid19

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
As of July 27, the #TaskForce has mapped #Covid19 #redzones in 53 #cities/#regencies located in 15 provinces, for further #mitigation #efforts.
#IndonesianWay #COVID19indonesia #indonesiamelawancovid19

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Based on the total #Covid19 cases per 1 million people by July 27, the<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>#TaskForce for the Acceleration of the Response to #Covid19 said that <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>ranked 142nd out of 215 countries globally,& 28th out of 49 countries in Asia.
#IndonesianWay #COVID19indonesia #indonesiamelawancovid19 https://t.co/jfn29Ser6R

text:
The #clinicaltrial of #Covid19 #vaccines is expected to complete in Jan 2021,using a total of 1,620 #samples, involving <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>'s #health #stakeholders; @biofarmaID,the Health Ministry (@Kemenkes),the Food&Drug Supervisory Agency(@BPOM_RI),&Padjadjaran Univ @Unpad.
.
#Covid19Indonesia

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
On July 19, PT @biofarmaID, a #state-owned #pharmaceutical #company, received #potential #Covid19 #vaccines developed by biopharmaceutical #company #Sinovac #Biotech for further #clinicaltrial.
.
#RintisKemajuan #Indonesianway #COVID19indonesia #indonesiamelawancovid19 #Vaccine

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>Govt implements #two-pronged #strategy to ensure #access to #Covid19 #vaccines: through #international #cooperation (#short-#term), & by establishing #national #vaccines #consortium (#mid-& #long-#term).
.
#IndonesianWay #RintisKemajuan #COVID19indonesia #BersamaLawanCorona https://t.co/umaJ9XHscM

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The New Committee coordinates two different #TaskForces; namely #TaskForce for the #National #EconomicRecovery& #Transformation, & #TaskForce for the #Acceleration of the #Response to #COVID19.
.
#IndonesianWay #COVID19indonesia #GlobalPandemic

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Recognizing that #Covid19 has a parallel #impact on #health& #economy, Pres @Jokowi assigned the #Covid19 Handling&Nat'l #EconomicRecovery Committee, led by the Coordinating Minister for the Economy, to maintain #economic #growth& curb the #pandemic in<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>.
.
#IndonesianWay https://t.co/gX3anaEfB8

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>Govt continues to expedite the #infrastructure #projects across the<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>archipelago amid the #Covid19pandemic while maintaining the #healthprotocols. The #construction #industry contributes as many as 10% of the nat'l #Gross #Domestic #Product.
#RintisKemajuan #COVID19indonesia https://t.co/rPnkRolV5E

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
4) Accelerate the process of #digitalpayments #system to expedite the #implementation of the #economy& #digital #finance as part of the #economicrecovery #efforts.
.
#RintisKemajuan #GlobalPandemic #EconomyOnTrack

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
3) Strengthen #coordination with the #Government& #Financial #System #Stability #Committee (#KSSK) in order to maintain #macroeconomic & #financial #system #stability.
.
#RintisKemajuan #GlobalPandemic #EconomyOnTrack

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
2) Strengthen #synergy of #monetary #expansion by accelerating the #Govt's #fiscal #stimulus through the #purchase of #Govt's #bonds fr the #primary #market & #sharing the #burden w/the Govt to accelerate the #recovery of #MSMEs& #business sectors.
#RintisKemajuan #EconomyOnTrack

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>Central Bank issued the #policies to support the Indonesian #Govt’s #economicrecovery #efforts:

1) Continue to bolster #Rupiah stabilization #policy in line with the #currency's #fundamental #value& #market #mechanisms.
.
#RintisKemajuan #GlobalPandemic #EconomyOnTrack

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>Central Bank estimated that the #global #economy was expected to take longer to #recover, as the #Covid19 #new #cases continue to grow & the #economic #mobility has not returned to normal, worsened by increasing #geopolitical #tensions.
.
#GlobalPandemic #EconomyOnTrack

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The decision was made after considering factors including #low #inflationary #pressure, maintained external #stability, & the #need to speed up #economicrecovery during the #CoronavirusPandemic.
.
#RintisKemajuan #EconomyOnTrack #Covid19Indonesia

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
To support nat'l #economicrecovery fr the #Covid-19 #pandemic, the<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>Central Bank cut its benchmark #interestrates, the BI 7-day #reverse repo rate, by 25 basis points(bps) to 4%,& lowered its deposit #facility rate to 3.25% &its #lending #facility rate to 4.75%.
.
#RintisKemajuan https://t.co/HFpjZDJBfS

#RintisKemajuan #wastemanagement #environment #energy #energyefficiency

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:

#RintisKemajuan https://t.co/Ypf6JQbJW7

text:
Some highlighted points fr the guidance:
*speed limit approaching 1mile radius is max 10knots, approaching 50m radius is 2knots
*boats should maintain min 30m distance from the whale sharks
*u should never touch/feed the #whalesharks

#IndonesianWay #SharkWeek https://t.co/4NvWJjTOFa

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Make sure to only book your #WhaleWatching #vacation in #WonderfulIndonesia w/ licensed #ecotourism operator & when u're there, also help us ensure ur #touroperator follows this guidance by our Min. of Marine & Fisheries Affairs @kkpgoid.
#IndonesianWay #TravelTomorrow #sharkweek https://t.co/TlPrALvjjT

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The growing numbers of #healthy #sharks in <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>#marine #nationalparks, incl the largest #WhaleShark #sanctuary-#CendrawasihBay, & newfound #shark #hotspots across the #archipelago, shows <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>govt&ppl's #awareness of the importance of #shark sustainability & #conservation.

#SharkWeek https://t.co/GXeLnKLofj

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>Min. of Marine Affairs&Fisheries listed #WhaleShark as 1 of the fully-protected marine species in <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>. Along w/ several regional govts, @kkpgoid implemented #regulations & #patrols to ensure #sustainable #fisheries, #ecotourism, & #conservation.
#IndonesianWay #OurOceanOurFuture

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Other areas in #WonderfulIndonesia to see or even swim w/ #WhaleSharks incl. #Probolinggo-#Java, #Botubarani-#Sulawesi, #Anambas-#Riau/#Sumatra, #Kaimana & #CendrawasihBay-#Papua, Talisayan-#Kalimantan, w/ the last 2 being #sanctuary for #sharks.

#Sharkweek #Diving #Ecotourism

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Be ready for unexpected surprises when you're sailing in #WonderfulIndonesia, such as @putriviona's encounter w/ Whale Sharks around #Flores-East Nusa Tenggara (#NTT) --1 of several areas in <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9> #archipelago where #WhaleSharks can be found!

#TravelThursday #IndonesianWay @WWF_ID https://t.co/fw8HfKXzSb

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#DidYouKnow that #WhaleShark also hv existed since app. 60mill. yrs ago? Despite being the largest #shark, it's moving on avg 3miles/hr. Thus, our govt released guidance for #touring & #swimming for the #safety of #visitors & these gentle #sharks.

#WonderfulIndonesia #SharkWeek

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#DidYouKnow that #WhaleShark is the largest living #fish ever found in the ocean? Although the baby is only 1.5-2ft long, weighing avg 1.4pounds, the species w/ up to 100yrs lifespan can grow to >32ft & weigh up to >20tons, despite eating solely #planktons&small fish.

#SharkWeek

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Thanks @Padi for continuously sharing #WonderfulIndonesia's #marine wonders!
It's even possible to find more #whalesharks in 1 #dive in #CendrawasihBay #NationalPark-#Papua @BalaiBesarTNTC, largest #WhaleShark #sanctuary w/ >130whale sharks living in the area (accord. to @WWF_ID) https://t.co/PQrTJiXqGl

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#Strategic #discussions with #members of the #USCongress is part of the #Indonesian #Embassy's #commitment to #promoting #ASEAN in the US while serving as the #Chair of #ACW for the period of May-August 2020.
.
#IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #SoutheastAsia #ASEANinUS

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The #discussion addressed some #topics of common concern in relation to #developments in the #region,int'l efforts to handle #COVID19pandemic,as well possible future #initiatives to enhance&strengthen US-ASEAN #Cooperation.
.
#IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #SoutheastAsia #ASEANinUS

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Under the <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>'s #Chairmanship,the #ASEAN #Committee in Washington,D.C.(#ACW) organized a #strategic #virtual #discussion w/Co-Chair of the @ASEANCaucus in the USCongress,Rep.Joaquin Castro,on Thursday(16/7).
.
#IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #SoutheastAsia #ASEANinUS @JoaquinCastrotx https://t.co/wA3a1d2UTF

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The #coordination #meeting also discussed #potential #strategic #engagements for the #ACW for the next 1.5 month under the #Indonesia's #Chairmanship.
.
#IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #SoutheastAsia #ASEANinUS

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Those #engagements were intended to promote #ASEAN in the #US and to discuss and formulate #potential #cooperation in a number of #different #diplomatic and #policy areas, including how to address the #COVID19pandemic. 
.
#IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #SoutheastAsia #ASEANinUS

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
From the end of April to June 2020, ACW has organized a number of #engagements with #senior #officials from the #US #Administration, #international #organizations, as well as #business #community.
.
#IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #SoutheastAsia #ASEANinUS

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
On Thursday (16/7), as the Chair of #ASEAN #Committee in Washington, D.C. (#ACW), the #Indonesian Embassy held a #coordination #meeting for #ASEAN Ambassadors to review the #Committee's activities over the past two months.
.
#IniDiplomasi #IndonesianWay #SoutheastAsia #ASEANinUS https://t.co/LoRZWOTx56

We hope they'll inspire u to learn more abt sharks & to join us in #conserving #sharks & all #OurOcean #biodiversity.

#WonderfulWednesday

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#Sharks are crucial in maintaining a healthy balance in the #ocean #ecosystem. At the top of the ocean #foodchain, sharks help to eliminate weak&sick members of ocean #fish #species&keep the whole system in balance.

#Shark #SharkAwarenessDay #DigitalDiplomacy @kkpgoid @OurOcean

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#DidYouKnow that #WonderfulIndonesia is <U+0001F3E0> to at least 117 #shark #species?
<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9> is committed to protect our sharks & all #marine #biodiversity, i.a. through strict #fishery & #ecotourism #regulations, as well as designating some areas as #sanctuary for #sharks.

#IndonesianWay

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Commemorating #SharkAwarenessDay & #SharkWeek, our #WordWednesday for #today is "ikan hiu".
Can u guess the English word?
.
.
It's #shark! <U+0001F988>
https://t.co/CVGm10sW8P

#LetsSpeakBahasaIndonesia #IkanHiu
@FSIatState @PeaceCorps @DCculture @EmbassyAdoption @DCGlobalEd @mullylingua

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The strong #collaboration between the <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>#Ministries & #Institutions, the #Local #Govt of #CentralKalimantan Province & the #participation of the province’s #residents are crucial to the #success of the #Food #Estate #program.
.
#RintisKemajuan #Foodsecurity #foodsovereignty

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
At the end of previous month, svrl Ministers made a #preliminary #visit to the designated #Food #Estate, incl Coord. Min. of #Economic Affairs, Min. of #Agrarian&Spatial #Planning &VM of #Trade, accompanied by the Gov of #CentralKalimantan.
.
#RintisKemajuan @atr_bpn @Kemendag https://t.co/Cy5dP7R2Ne

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Along w/better #irrigation #system prepared by the @KemenPU, @Kementan will develop the #cultivation #tech f/#planting to boost the #production #capacity fr 1-2tons per hectare to 3-4tons per hectare. Whereas @KemenBUMN is responsible f/the #investment #scheme.
.
#RintisKemajuan https://t.co/byPL0Z4q15

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Out of 85,500 hectares of the #functional #land, around 28,300 hectares has good #irrigation, while other 57,200 hectares need further #rehabilitation on the #irrigation #channels. 
.
#RintisKemajuan #foodsecurity #foodsafety #foodsovereignty https://t.co/dVLtF7n6IL

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The designated #Estate does not require #clearing new #tracts of #land, since the area of 85,500hectares is a #functional #land that has been used for #production every year, while the remaining 79,500hectares is in the form of #shrubs that need further #clearing.
#RintisKemajuan https://t.co/XPxfNviJfw

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The #Food #Estate #Area is prepared on the #alluvial #area (not #peat #land) of 165,000 hectares on the Ex-#Peatlands #Development (#PLG) #land in #CentralKalimantan, to be built in 2020-2022.
.
#RintisKemajuan #foodsecurity #foodsafety #foodsovereignty https://t.co/qdfUNHTVD2

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Recognizing the importance of #foodsecurity as part of #national #defense, Pres @Jokowi appointed Ministry of Defense as the leading sector of the #Food #Estate #program. 
#RintisKemajuan #foodsafety #foodsovereignty @Kemhan_RI https://t.co/hQtjVxwBi1

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The #development of the #Food #Estate #program, involving several ministries, is an anticipatory #measure amid #concerns over possible #global #food #crisis due to the ongoing #COVID19pandemic, as previously assessed by the @FAO.
#RintisKemajuan #foodsecurity @FAOIndonesia https://t.co/n8EBUHiA5m

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Pres @Jokowi inspected the designated #Food #Estate #Area in Kapuas&Pulang Pisau, #CentralKalimantan Prov, accompanied by several Ministers along w/the #Gov&other officials. The #Food #Estate is part of the #National #Strategic #Programs 2020-2024.
#RintisKemajuan #foodsecurity https://t.co/5qStFSmeeb

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>'s #diplomacy is actively pursuing #equitable& #affordable #access to #Covid19 #vaccines,particularly through #multilateral #fora. Meanwhile,exploring #innovative #ways at #home incl by #developing local Covid19 vaccines remains critically #important.

#RintisKemajuan @Menlu_RI https://t.co/AQnBdENAKO

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: Had a good discussion with Vice Minister of State Owned Enteprises (H.E. Budi Gunadi Sadikin) and Biofarma, detailing international cooperation and preparations for clinical trials of Covid-19 vaccine (Bandung, 15/7) https://t.co/8vyxw5AlFn

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: Had a thorough discussion on the development of the Covid-19 pandemic at the national, regional as well as global level with the WHO Representative to Indonesia, Navaratnasamy Paranietharan @NParanietharan (14/07) https://t.co/8zOAcSKI94

.

.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>Govt is going to #redesign the #irrigation #system in the #planned #Food #Estate #Area, since an #inefficient #irrigation #system would cause the #low #productivity&hinder the #flow of #water& #optimal #fertilizer #absorption.
#RintisKemajuan #IndonesianWay #foodsecurity

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Pres @Jokowi accompanied by a number of ministers visited the #Irrigation #Improvement #Acceleration #Program(P3TGAI),located in Pulang Pisau #Regency,#CentralKalimantan Prov,to inspect the #labor-#intensive #projects f/people in #rural areas during the #pandemic.
#RintisKemajuan https://t.co/2CME37DVKv

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Despite being called #durian (the word 'duri' means ’spike'), #DurianGundul (means 'bald #durian') is spikeless & looks similar to #coconut.

Those who hate the #smell should try #Kalimantan's #DurianPampakin, w/ orange-color-flesh, which has low alcohol level, thus less-smelly.

text:

#Nowadays, the locals wear #Khombow for 3 spc purposes--a #newborn wrap, a woman's #weddingdress, & a #corpse wrap.
#Khombow Trees aren't very easily found, thus some also start creating Khombow #art on other tree #barks to #conserve both #nature & #culture.

#conservationmatters

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#Khombow #bark #paintings used to be made&worn as #clothing only by the #Ondofolo (highest leader).
Thus, certain patterns are #sacred to be made&worn by the Ondofolo only.
Each tribe also has specific #patterns based on their own #culturalheritage & #experiences.

#IndonesianArt

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The #Khombow #bark #painting has been done for centuries using #natural #dyes & #traditional tools.
The #patterns were inspired by their daily #nature encounters, ranging fr the sun up to the protected #freshwater #sharks, #sawfish, living in the #Sentani #Lake.

#IndonesianWay

text:

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
We take this opportunity to recognize and commend the long-standing efforts of all relevant parties, including those of Qatar and the United States, in supporting the peace process in Afghanistan. 

Berlin / Doha / Jakarta / Oslo / Tashkent 
24 May 2020

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: Statement Agreed by the Foreign Ministers of Germany, Indonesia, Norway, Uzbekistan, and Qatar on 24 May

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: In this connection, we also encourage the taking of necessary measures to protect vulnerable groups and individuals, including prisoners, from the pandemic.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: As like-minded countries resolved to co-operate in our support for an inclusive peace process in Afghanistan, we stand ready to assist the process in any way the parties may wish.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
On its part, Indonesia is committed to continue its contribution for the future of Afghanistan.

Indonesia wishes all Afghans a blessed and peaceful Eid

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: Indonesia hopes it would provide momentum for a sustainable peace and stability in Afghanistan.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: Indonesia welcomes the ceasefire announcement by the Government of Afghanistan and the Taliban during the Eid al-Fitr.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
We hope you enjoy this #IndonesianWay #RamadanTradition series of #FoodFriday. We hope u're inspired to search for the recipes as u #StayAtHome or put them down in ur #WonderfulIndonesia #BucketList for ur visit in future #Ramadan.
Wishing you a blessed last week of #Ramadan2020.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#DidYouKnow that it has been a #Tambrauw tradition to have the #Christians become #EidAlFitr prep committee & the #Muslims become the #Christmas prep committee?

#IndonesianWay #PapuaSolid #UnityinDiversity

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Although similar to #Javanese #pia (round pastry w/ #mungbean filling), #PiaTambrauw contains #coconutoil&it's grilled in fire.
As the majority of the locals prefers savory than sweet #pastry, the Pia's slight-savory-smoky-taste makes it a favored #iftar opener&year-round snack.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
'Kue Lontar' is a famous Papuan milk pie, which may vary fr 1 area to another. For example, in #Tambrauw, it is commonly found in rectangle/square-shape, rather than circle-shape in other areas. It is commonly served w/ hot coffee/tea.
#FoodFriday #RamadanTradition #IndonesianWay

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Among them is #CantikManis, a pink-green, steamed cupcake, which uses #pandan& #coconutmilk, along w/ sugar, egg & flour.
#DidYouKnow that in #BahasaIndonesia, 'cantik' means pretty, while 'manis' means sweet?
#FoodFriday #RamadanTradition #IndonesianWay #Papua2020 @culinarydiplo

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
As more ppl fr South Sulawesi come to #Tambrauw-West #Papua, not only do they enrich the #diversity in the area, but their recipes & the locals' also influenced one another, resulting in some of the popular #Iftar opener sold in the local markets during #Ramadan.

#IndonesianWay https://t.co/2kGE9Gn6jM

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#Popaco is another sweet&savory #iftar opener in #Ternate-#Maluku/#Moluccas.
It is made from #tapioca #starch, #riceflour, & #coconutmilk steamed in #PandanLeaf molds.

#RamadanTradition #IndonesianWay #FoodFriday @CulinaryDiplo #Ramadan2020 https://t.co/NEQfaS5sBf

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#WadahIpau is another #RamadanTradition fr #Banjarmasin-South #Kalimantan, as it's only sold in the #RamadanMarket. It has unique sweet&savory blend fr having beef-filling & being served w/ #coconutcream & minced celery-shallots toppings.
#FoodFriday #IndonesianWay @CulinaryDiplo https://t.co/hVjhuHNPWk

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#Sotong means #cuttlefish & 'Pakong' means 'hit'. #SotongPangkong, a favored #iftar opener fr <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>equator city, #Pontianak-West #Kalimantan, is made fr dried cuttlefish, served w/ spicy peanut sweet-sour, spiced dried shrimp sauce.

#RamadanTradition #FoodFriday #IndonesianWay https://t.co/xCZbzw0wOT

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#PutuCangkir is made from a mixture of black&white glutinous rice, grated coconut & palm sugar molded using oil funnel & steamed. It is a #RamadanTradition in #Makassar-South Sulawesi, where it is commonly enjoyed w/ the local coffee/tea.
@culinarydiplo #FoodFriday #IndonesianWay https://t.co/s8CpaFTZNA

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
A popular #iftar opener fr #Gresik-East #Java, #BongkoKopyor, contains var. ingredients, incl. #bread pcs, young #coconut meat, #banana, #jackfruit, #tapiocapearls, #coconutmilk & #pandanleaf--all are wrapped&steamed in #bananaleaves.

#RamadanTradition #FoodFriday #IndonesianWay https://t.co/Rw4aOPFzOz

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#Gulai is 1 of <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9> types of curry, which originated in #Sumatera & normally has yellowish color fr the #turmeric. #GulaiSiput is conch curry, a popular #RamadanTradition fr #Tanjungpinang-#Riau Islands, as it is only sold during #Ramadan.

#FoodFriday #IndonesianWay @culinarydiplo https://t.co/jKhl4hoBtZ

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Despite having a slight bitter taste as #Pakat are mainly grilled young #rattan shoots, it is a popular #iftar opener in #Mandailing Natal-North #Sumatera.

#RamadanTradition #IndonesianWay #FoodFriday #Ramadan2020 #WonderfulIndonesia @culinarydiplo https://t.co/q7cxnDNaY2

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
It might look like #spaghetti, but this is #MiCaluk: stick-shaped-noodle served in banana leaf, w/ nut gravy containing chili&various local spices, commonly sold during #Ramadan in #Pidie-#Aceh-our westernmost province.

#RamadanTradition #IndonesianWay #FoodFriday @CulinaryDiplo https://t.co/JCHqSySYyX

text:
Released on Aug29, 2019,#Gundala attracted more than 1millions moviegoers 7days after it hit <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>’s cinemas. The film is adapted fr the1960s comic book series by Hasmi Suryaminata&is expected to reach the US by July28. Proud of you,#Gundala!
#RintisKemajuan #Creative @Kemenparekraf https://t.co/jf6c6TCPSc

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>Govt continues to increase the capacity of svrl referral hospitals f/#Covid19 such as those in the regencies of #Lamongan in @JatimPemprov& #BiakNumfor in @PemprovPapua,as an anticipative measure to better handle the #covid19.
#IndonesianWay #IndonesiaMelawanCovid19 #Papua https://t.co/bzhWRSjBQ7

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
This is due in part to the crucial role of about 1500 #traditional #village committees in helping increase Balinese’s #awareness about the importance of #discipline& #order during #COVID19Pandemic.
#IndonesianWay #togetheragainstcovid19 #TogetherWeCan #IndonesiaPastiBisa #local

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Popular tourist destinations may risk becoming fertile grounds f/ #Covid19. #Bali, however, has reported relatively low virus fatality rate among <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>’s hardest hit regions. 
#IndonesianWay #IndonesiaMelawanCovid19 #TogetherWeCan #TravelTomorrow #AfterCovid19 #aftercorona #Local https://t.co/EIcIFguEX2

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
A police appeared at the Sempidi #TraditionalMarket,#Bali wearing a celuluk #costume& #gloves w/a #Covid19 print to raise awareness about the measures against #COVID19. In Balinese #folklore,celuluk is an underling to the Queen of all #Leaks(#evil sorceres),Rangda.
#IndonesianWay https://t.co/40AlFh3BSl

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Amid plans to ease #PSBB in several regions, Pres @Jokowi underlined that such measures should be done carefully&based on data&facts from the field.
#IndonesianWay #NegaraMelindungi #IndonesiaMelawanCovid19 #TogetherWeSolve #TogetherWeCan #StayHomeSaveLives #PhysicalDistancing https://t.co/a7zbrWpjEN

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The Syekh had shown intelligence, artistry & fine character since he was young that the Sultan took him to be raised in the palace along w/ the Sultan's kids.
He became a renowned figure not only throughout <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>, but also in Malacca, Philippines, India, Egypt, Turkey, Mecca&Medina.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The #GrandMosque is named #SabilalMuhtadin, a famous holy book written by an Islamic scholar & prolific writer of various subject, Syekh Muh. Arsyad al-Banjari, who was born in a village by #Martapura river, #Banjarmasin-#Kalimantan, where the #mosque is located.

#TravelThursday https://t.co/W0NXJ16Vd3

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#MasjidAgungIbnuBatutah (Ibnu Batutah #GreatMosque) is located in #PujaMandala Worship Complex, #NusaDua-#Bali, alongside houses of #worship of other religions: #Catholic #church, #Protestant church, #Buddhist #Temple, & #Hindu temple.

#Ramadan2020 #TravelThursday #IndonesianWay https://t.co/SHmZu1QxTT

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Built in 1560 during the era of #Banten's 1st Sultan--who was also son of Sunan Gunung Jati (1 of the #WaliSongo), #MasjidAgungBanten has a pagoda-shaped building designed by a Chinese architect & a 24m (app 79ft) tower designed by a Dutch architect.

#Ramadan2020 #IndonesianWay https://t.co/kav6uv9Gez

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
#SunanAmpel, 1 of the #WaliSongo, was married to the princess of #Majapahit (Hindu kingdom of the area) after the Sunan's father was invited by the king to solve the gambling problem. He used the #mosque for teaching place, & his grave can be found in the area.

#Ramadan2020

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Built by Sunan Ampel in 1421, #AmpelMosque which is located in the #Arabic kampung of #Surabaya-#Java, is the 3rd oldest in<U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>&2nd largest in the city. It has ancient Javanese architecture&5 curved-gates representing the 5pillars of #Islamic teaching
#IndonesianWay #TravelThursday https://t.co/RuiOUvTmkW

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
When you get to visit this #mosque #aftercorona, see if you can recognize the influence of #Morocco, #Europe, #Malay, & #MiddleEast in the #mosque, along w/ Italian & German #marbles, & Chinese #stainedglass.

#IndonesianWay #TravelThursday #TravelTomorrow #WonderfulIndonesia

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Also known as #MasjidAlMashun, #Medan #GrandMosque was built b/w 1906-1909 by a Sultan who wanted it to be more majestic than his #MaimunPalace. He recruited a Dutch designer & had some of the materials imported from other countries.

#IndonesianWay #Ramadan2020 #TravelThursday https://t.co/hsWZd2nIsl

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
For #today&next week's #TravelThursday, we will take you to visit mosques throughout <U+0001F1EE><U+0001F1E9>#archipelago with unique #architecture and/or #history, as we are entering the last 2 weeks of #Ramadhan. Make sure to visit them when you visit #WonderfulIndonesia #aftercorona.
#IndonesianWay

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The Region Promotional Film category,“#Lake #Toba–The Biggest Caldera Lake in the World”&the Eco-tourism Promotional Clip category,“#RajaAmpat–The King of the Ocean”won #awards at the 16th #ITFF in #Bulgaria.<U+0001F44D><U+0001F44D>&Way to go further in promoting #WonderfulIndonesia!
#RintisKemajuan https://t.co/bHjA2qxDkB

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The economy&social infrastructures at the Integrated Cross-Border Posts (#PLBN) of #Aruk-#WestKalimantan, #Motaain-#EastNusaTenggara,& #Skouw-#Papua are expected to keep supporting the #MSMEs particularly during #Covid19pandemic.
#IndonesianWay #RintisKemajuan #StandTogether https://t.co/VOAGTf6YtX

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Among the #community #services carried out by the #Indonesian Army in #Papua are #medical #treatment to the people living in the East Arom district of Keerom Regency at the #Indonesia-#PNG border area.
#IndonesianWay #NegaraMelindungi #papuasolid #StandTogether #TogetherWeCan https://t.co/Gyu3DqIeyL

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
For sure, the hardships during the #COVID19pandemic do not reduce #Indonesia’s #humanitarian spirit to provide support to the people of #Fiji as #Cyclone #Harold battered that country on Apr 8. Our thoughts are with you!
#IndonesianWay #Solidarity #StandTogether #TogetherWeRise https://t.co/NmFr2uuoYk

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The #Covid19 recovery rate in #Bali hs reached around 66% &it is targeted by Bali Prov Govt at 90% by the end of May. Good coordination among the #local authorities to the lowest layers along w/the strict discipline of the people lead to the positive trend in Bali.
#IndonesianWay https://t.co/gqTV78Depn

#IniDiplomasi #againstCOVID19 #GlobalPandemic #GlobalSolidarity #GlobalUnity #BersamaLawanCorona https://t.co/RvREBuZJAK

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
President @Jokowi underlined the importance of concerted @ASEAN response against the #COVID19 pandemic.

#IniDiplomasi #againstCOVID19 #GlobalPandemic #GlobalSolidarity #GlobalUnity #BersamaLawanCorona #ASEAN #StrongerTogether #TogetherAgainstCovid19 https://t.co/S26txdx3dI

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: It is importance for APT to lead the way in ensuring the region continues to be the engine of global economic growth as well as the anchor for regional resilience.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: President Jokowi called for APT unity and strengthen cooperation to increase resilience in facing Covid-19 and strengthen economic cooperation for economic resilience. https://t.co/pWcJB7oMOL

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: President Jokowi is confident that ASEAN Plus Three, established on the back of a crisis in 1999, will once again prove its resiliency in facing Covid-19.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Held back to back with ASEAN Special Summit, President @Jokowi joined the virtual Special ASEAN plus Three (APT) Summit on Covid-19 from Bogor Palace (14/4)

#ASEANPlusThree #ASEAN2020VN https://t.co/gxfwXPktxx

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: ASEAN Leaders also agreed to combat Covid-19 through sharing of knowledge and best practices in R&D of epidemiology and development of anti-viral drugs and vaccines.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: Indonesia supported the consideration of the establishment of ASEAN COVID-19 Response Fund, especially for the procurement of essential medical equipment.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: President Jokowi emphasized the importance: (1) ensure unhindered flow of goods in the region, especially food, medicines, and medical equipment; (2) protect ASEAN citizens and migrant workers; (3) collaborate with ASEAN external partners. https://t.co/8iVcuCCkOX

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
To break the chain of infection, Indonesia proposed development of ASEAN protocol to respond to Covid-19 at borders, through joint contact tracing and outbreak investigation.
#ASEAN2020VN

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
The virtual ASEAN Special Summit on Covid-19 was held this morning (14/04). President Jokowi joined other ASEAN leaders from Istana Bogor.

President @Jokowi underlined the importance of unity, synergy and cooperation between #ASEAN countries in facing the pandemic. https://t.co/Zf929NOneS

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: Indonesia’s foreign policy for 2020 will focus on 4+1: economic diplomacy, protection diplomacy, sovereign and national identity diplomacy, Indonesia’s leading role in the regional and global stage, and strengthening diplomatic infrastructure.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: On economic diplomacy, in 2020 Indonesia will focus on a number of economic cooperation negotiation; organize a number of international events including WEF on ASEAN & Indo-Pacific & Halal Industry Summit; and attract quality investment to support sustainable growth in Indonesia https://t.co/1xjC92lJhV

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: On protection diplomacy, Indonesia will apply a holistic strategy at national and international level. The presence of the state in the protection of Indonesian citizens will continue to be reinforced at all levels.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: On sovereignty and national identity diplomacy, Indonesia will intensify land and maritime negotiations; protect Indonesian territorial integrity; and mainstream issues deemed as national assets including pluralism, democracy, tolerance, and women empowerment.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: On strengthening diplomatic infrastructure, MOFA will continue to take reform and efficiency measures and fortify information and communication technology infrastructures at the headquarters and in Indonesian missions abroad

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: Indonesia will also continue to defend the Palestinian issue; support Afghanistan peace process; and promote the interest of the Ummah around the world.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: On regional and global role, Indonesia will continue to contribute and be part of solutions for the global challenges, including through ASEAN, UNSC and UN Human Rights Council.

text: OIC must be the real beacon of a peaceful Islam and pursue more dialogues and peaceful initiatives - Ret https://t.co/QtAKdSKgdK

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: On top of the seven points, I call on OIC members to reinforce commitments towards OIC Contact Group for Peace and Dialogue as platform to deal with Islamphobia and all kinds of discrimination.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: Seventh: as the Ummah is facing enormous challenges, OIC must stand United and firm in addressing the real problem of Ummah, such as discrimination against Muslim and oppression against Palestinian.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:
Fifth: We must reinforce the value of tolerance. Peaceful coexistence can only be built upon a strong foundation of tolerance

Sixth: we must re-double efforts in promoting interfaith dialogue. Christchurch compels us to strengthen  our global collaboration in promoting dialogue.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: Fourth: Christchurch is a reminder that no country is immune from terrorism. Christchurch is a testament of the lack of understanding about Islam as religion of peace.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: Third: as a member of UNSC, Indonesia-together with Kuwait, initiated a UN Security Council press statement expressing the strongest condemnation toward Christchruch attacks.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:

Security Council reaffirmed that terrorism in all its forms and manifestations constitutes one of the most serious threats to international peace and security.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text:

I offered any assistance needed by New Zealand in this time of sorrow.

text: Just communicated with  Foreign Minister Stef Blok of Netherlands and conveyed deepest condolences and sympathies on the shooting that took place in Utrecht earlier today.(18/03)

text: Had a meeting with the Charge d'Affairs of New Zealand Embassy (18/3). I conveyed once again my condolences and sympathies to the families and friends of the victims of the Christchurch attack. https://t.co/BMmCQpc9t5

text:

Indonesia and Australia agreed to strengthen cooperation on the promotion of tolerance.

text: I met the Ambassador of Australia, H.E. Mr. Gary Quinlan and conveyed Indonesia's strong condemnation towards the statement of Senator Fraser Anning of Queensland on New Zealand Mosque Shooting (18/03) https://t.co/RLLLWmHMRX

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: The President of @IMAAMCenter, Mr Bagus Adiyanto extended the community's warm welcome to Amb Siregar and family, and reiterated the Center's long-standing commitment as an important partner to support the mission of the Embassy.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: Amb. Siregar also hoped that IMAAM Center extended and shared its best practices as an effective and respected Muslim organization to other Indonesian and local organizations.

name: IndonesianEmbassy DC
text: In his remarks, Amb. Siregar underlined IMAAM Center's strategic role as an important asset of Indonesian diplomacy and praised its enduring role in representing the face of peaceful Islam in Indonesia to the local public. https://t.co/4hu8dWhnWR
